# Dragon's Ledger — environment template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 1 (local-first) needs NO environment variables or secrets at all.
# This file exists only to document the seam for Phase 2.
#
# When you swap the LocalDataProvider for a realtime backend (see
# src/lib/data/README in the architecture walkthrough), the backend's
# connection details go here. Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is
# git-ignored) and fill in real values. NEVER commit `.env.local`.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 2 — multiplayer (frontend)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Point this at your self-hosted WebSocket server to enable real-time
# multiplayer. When UNSET, the app runs in pure local/solo mode (Phase 1).
# Local dev:  ws://localhost:8787
# Production: wss://your-server-host        (TLS required for wss://)
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and set the value there.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MULTIPLAYER_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8787
#
# The server's own secrets (AUTH_SECRET, DB_PATH, PORT) live in server/.env —
# see server/.env.example. They are NEVER needed by the frontend.
